[Name] SHFS
[Summary] Mounts remote directories using a shell connection.
[License] GNU General Public License (GPL)
[Description] SHFS (sshfs) is a simple and easy-to-use Linux kernel module which allows you to mount remote filesystems using a plain shell (SSH) connection. It supports some nice
features like file cache for access speedup, and a Perl server, etc.
[Homepage] http://shfs.sourceforge.net/
